# Plan тАФ auction-scraper

**STATUS: READY** тАФ research integrated. No open unknowns. Proceed to demo-builder.

---

## 1. Demo Concept

**Auction Scraper Console** тАФ live multi-source Python scraper with streaming dashboard.

Click "Run Scraper" тЖТ SSE stream opens тЖТ 3 real auction sources scraped in parallel тЖТ lot cards accumulate in real time with images, estimates, sale dates тЖТ JSON inspector shows raw vs normalized schema тЖТ rate-limit telemetry log shows pacing + retries + the `flagged_for_api` event when Heritage blocks. The demo IS the proposal: it proves scraping depth, tool judgment, and responsible-scraping posture.

---

## 2. Prototype vs Full

**Full.** Richness 10. Every feature is real and working. Seeded Heritage fallback is a safety net, not the default. No prototype tripwire triggers.

---

## 3. Sources (confirmed by research)

| Source | Tool | Crawl Delay | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Leland Little** (lelandlittle.com) | `requests` + BeautifulSoup | 2s | Fully open robots.txt, static HTML, USD |
| **Heritage Auctions** (ha.com) | Playwright + JSON-LD extraction | 15s | Likely 403 in prod тЖТ emit `flagged_for_api` + serve seeded fallback |
| **Bonhams** (bonhams.com) | Playwright + `/_next/data` intercept | 3s | Next.js, JS-rendered, estimates in GBP/EUR |

Tool judgment is explicit and demonstrable тАФ one static (requests+BS4), two JS-rendered (Playwright with different extraction strategies).

---

## 4. Normalized JSON Schema (per lot)

```json
{
  "source": "leland_little | heritage_auctions | bonhams",
  "source_url": "https://...",
  "lot_number": "string | null",
  "title": "string",
  "description": "string | null",
  "estimate_low": 500,
  "estimate_high": 800,
  "currency": "USD | GBP | EUR",
  "raw_estimate_text": "┬г3,000 тАУ 5,000",
  "sale_date": "2026-07-15",
  "bidding_deadline": "2026-07-15T18:00:00Z | null",
  "images": ["https://..."],
  "status": "upcoming | live | closed",
  "scraped_at": "2026-06-23T14:00:00Z",
  "scraper_notes": "string | null"
}
```

Normalization rules:
- Leland Little: estimates may be `null` pre-auction (scrape what's on detail page, normalize missing to `null` + note)
- Heritage: extract from JSON-LD `offers` block; expose raw JSON-LD in JSON inspector
- Bonhams: detect currency symbol from `raw_estimate_text` (┬г/тВм/$), parse low/high, set `currency`
- `bidding_deadline` = same as `sale_date` unless site distinguishes

---

## 5. Features

### Hero: Live Scrape + SSE Stream
- Frontend POSTs to `/demos/auction-scraper/scrape` with `{sources: [...]}` тЖТ returns `{job_id}`
- `EventSource` opens `/demos/auction-scraper/stream/<job_id>`
- Backend: one thread per source, results feed a shared `queue.Queue` consumed by SSE endpoint
- SSE event types:
  - `source_start` тАФ source name, tool being used
  - `lot` тАФ full normalized lot object тЖТ card rendered in UI
  - `rate_limit_pause` тАФ duration, request count (feeds telemetry log)
  - `retry` тАФ attempt #, delay
  - `flagged_for_api` тАФ source, reason (Heritage 403 тЖТ seeded lots emitted as `lot` events after)
  - `source_done` тАФ source, lot count, elapsed
  - `job_done` тАФ total count, elapsed тЖТ EventSource closes
- No polling, pure SSE push

### Supporting 1: JSON Inspector Panel
- Every lot card has a "{ }" button тЖТ slide-in panel with pretty-printed normalized JSON
- Heritage lots include collapsible "Raw JSON-LD" section (transformation story: raw Product schema тЖТ normalized lot)
- Global "View Dataset" button тЖТ full result array, copy button exports `auction-lots.json`
- Toggle: Raw JSON-LD тЖТ Normalized schema (Heritage only)

### Supporting 2: Image Rendering + Lightbox
- Backend image proxy: `GET /demos/auction-scraper/image?url=<encoded>` тАФ streams image bytes with `Referer` header set to source domain (bypasses CDN referrer checks)
- Lot cards: image thumbnail (150├Ч150, object-fit cover, left side of card)
- Click thumbnail тЖТ full-res lightbox modal
- No image тЖТ placeholder (auction-gavel SVG icon, styled per design)

### Supporting 3: Per-Source Telemetry Log
- Collapsible log panel, scrolling, newest at bottom
- Each `rate_limit_pause` / `retry` / `flagged_for_api` SSE event appends a timestamped line
- Example lines:
  - `[14:03:02] leland_little тАФ GET /items/12345 тЖТ 200 (2.1s delay)`
  - `[14:03:18] heritage_auctions тАФ flagged_for_api: 403 received тАФ serving cached lots`
  - `[14:03:21] bonhams тАФ retry 1/3, backoff 4s`
- Source status badges: IDLE тЖТ RUNNING тЖТ DONE (green) / FLAGGED (amber) / ERROR (red)
- Telemetry IS the answer to screening Q3 (rate limiting) тАФ proposal-writer should point to it

### Supporting 4: Filters + Export
- Filter bar: source checkboxes, "has image" toggle, estimate range slider
- Sort: sale date, estimate low, source
- Export current (filtered) dataset as `auction-lots.json` download
- (Scope fence: no search text; filters + sort is sufficient)

---

## 6. Backend Architecture

**Blueprint file:** `../mw-backend/auction_scraper_blueprint.py`
**URL prefix:** `/demos/auction-scraper`

Routes:
| Route | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/scrape` | POST | Start job. Body: `{sources:[...]}`. Returns `{job_id}`. Spawns threads. |
| `/stream/<job_id>` | GET | SSE stream (text/event-stream). Reads queue until `job_done`. |
| `/results/<job_id>` | GET | Full normalized array after completion. Cleans up job state. |
| `/image` | GET | Proxy: `?url=<encoded>`. Sets `Referer` to source domain. |
| `/health` | GET | `{ok:true, playwright_available:bool}` |

**Scraper modules** (in blueprint or sibling files):
```python
class BaseScraper:
    slug: str
    name: str
    rate_limit_s: float
    def scrape(self, event_queue: queue.Queue) -> None  # emits dicts to queue
```

Implementations: `LelandLittleScraper`, `HeritageAuctionsScraper`, `BonhamsScraper`

**Seeded fallback** (`auction_scraper_seeds.json` alongside blueprint): 8 real Heritage lots with JSON-LD structure + real image URLs. Emitted after `flagged_for_api` event with note in `scraper_notes`.

**Playwright:** Already installed in mw-backend. Health endpoint verifies chromium via `subprocess.run(["python", "-c", "from playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright"])`. demo-builder should run `playwright install chromium` on Surface if needed.

---

