## 12. Build Sequence

1. **demo-builder:**
   a. Write `auction_scraper_blueprint.py` + `auction_scraper_seeds.json` in `../mw-backend/`
   b. Register blueprint in `server.py`
   c. Build `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/auction-scraper/` (index.html, app.js, styles.css)
   d. Verify Playwright chromium on Surface via `/health` endpoint
   e. Add `workSamples.js` entry
   f. Create public GitHub repo + push scraper source
   g. Self-test: load demo locally, no console errors, click Run Scraper, verify SSE fires, cards appear, JSON inspector opens, telemetry log populates

2. **deploy:** push both repos; verify live URLs (site 200 + api health ok)

3. **deploy-test:** Playwright against live site тАФ click Run Scraper, verify SSE events arrive, lot cards render with images, JSON inspector opens for Heritage lot with raw JSON-LD, telemetry log shows rate_limit_pause event, export button downloads JSON

4. **media-capture:** screenshot mid-scrape (cards accumulating + telemetry active)

5. **proposal-writer:** cover letter starting BROCCOLI, answer 3 questions, link demo + GitHub, U.S. Bank ownership + Playwright history prominent

